#DStv403 #eNCA  JOHANNESBURG - The arrests of Atul and Rajesh Gupta have sent shockwaves throughout the world. The two were arrested in Dubai. However, the South African Justice Department says although they have been arrested, it is unlikely that they will appear in a South African court any time soon. WATCH | Dubai police: Gupta brothers facing extradition Acting US Ambassador to SA, Heather Merritt, says this shows what can be done when countries work together. At the same time, the National Prosecuting Authority has confirmed it is working with officials in the UAE to extradite the Gupta brothers. Watch the video above for more details on this story. 